  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nAs reported by @axic, migrations are failing against `geth --dev` networks\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n\r\n1. `truffle init`\r\n2. Uncomment the `\"development\"` network in truffle-config.js\r\n3. (In another terminal) `geth --dev --rpc`\r\n4. `truffle migrate`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nMigration to succeed.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nStarting migrations...\r\n======================\r\n> Network name:    'development'\r\n> Network id:      1337\r\n> Block gas limit: 0x5fdfb1\r\n\r\n\r\n1_initial_migration.js\r\n======================\r\n\r\n   Deploying 'Migrations'\r\n   ----------------------\r\nError: Error: Error:  *** Deployment Failed ***\r\n\r\n\"Migrations\" exceeded the block limit (with a gas value you set).\r\n   * Block limit:  0x201ae63\r\n   * Gas sent:     6721975\r\n   * Try:\r\n      + Sending less gas.\r\n      + Setting a higher network block limit if you are on a\r\n        private network or test client (like ganache).\r\n\r\n    at Object.run (/.../truffle/build/webpack:/packages/truffle-migrate/index.js:92:1)\r\n    at <anonymous>\r\n    at process._tickCallback (internal/process/next_tick.js:189:7)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Mac\r\n* Ethereum client: Geth v1.9.2\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.33",
