    "body": "@gnidan @axic \r\n\r\nGeth dev's [starting block gas limit](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/cc9eb91d30a5d4806154b832b9665aecc617b6d8/core/genesis.go#L389) is lower than truffle's default \"gas sent\" for transactions...\r\n```\r\ngeth: 6,283,185\r\ntruffle: 6,721,975\r\n```\r\nA quick work-around is to set the `gas` param in the truffle config for the relevant network lower, (eg 6000000)\r\n\r\nThe block limit gas value in the error output is incorrect. It's getting mangled somewhere.  \r\n```\r\n* Block limit:  0x201ae63\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe block limit reported in the top layer is correct but should probably be in decimal:\r\n```\r\n> Block gas limit: 0x5fdfb1\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
